title: For Sale:  STAR MODEL B SUPER 9MM LUGER
postcontent: Star Model B Super. Chambered in 9mm Luger / parabellum. Made from 1946 to the end of classic-model production in 1983, model Bs with Super upgrades were produced. The major change is the replacement of the swinging link with a Sig 210 (or modern Star) style closed cam path integral to the barrel. Related to this, a full-length guide rod with captive spring, and a quick takedown lever were added as well. All of these models have a magazine safety, but one slightly different from the later S variants, and the extractor is modified to double as a loaded-chamber indicator. Additionally, the sights are improved in shape to make them easier to see, and minor changes were made to the trigger system. Condition: Used/Excellent. Light scuffs and light wear. There are also various tiny nicks and storage marks present. Bore is clean and bright.

title: For Sale:  Sale or sell????? English Lesson
postcontent:
Guy's, your ad's represent you. What kind of impression do you want to make with people? 
Sell" is a verb, an action, it requires conjugation: I sell, you sell, he sells.. I sold, you sold, and so on. "Sale" is a noun, it is not conjugated and usually would appear together with definite or undefinite article "the sale", "a sale".

When person A sold something, A made a sale.

Only five percent (about 1,850) of the estimated SPAS-12 shotguns manufactured were imported into the U.S. The SPAS-12 is a dual-mode shotgun, adjustable for semi-automatic or pump-action operation. The SPAS-12 has been sold to military and police users worldwide, on the civilian market, and has been featured in films and TV shows. The SPAS 12 was designed to function primarily as a semi-automatic firearm, with the pump-action mode used to reliably fire low-pressure ammunition such as tear gas rounds or less-lethal bean bags. The firing mode is switched by pressing a button under the foregrip and sliding the foregrip slightly forwards or backwards until it clicks into position. The SPAS-12 has a magazine cut-off feature, which prevents loading a new round from the internal magazine when the gun is cycled. This allows the operator to load a specialized round into the chamber without firing the entire magazine first. The barrel of the SPAS 12 was externally threaded to accept a variety of attachments, from chokes to gas-grenade launchers. The appearance and intended purpose of the SPAS-12 initially led to its "combat" designation. Franchi renamed the model the Sporting Purpose Automatic Shotgun in 1990, after the importation ban of 1989 (when it was called the Special Purpose Automatic Shotgun). This allowed continued sales to the U.S. as a limited-magazine-capacity, fixed-stock model until 1994. Following the Federal Assault Weapons Ban, exports to the U.S.

FOR CASH SALE

An Olympic Arms AR-15 Model M.F.R. 97.
If you are looking for a 'Safe Queen' or a 'Perfect LNIB Gun' this gun isn't for you.

This is an older AR that is fully functional but has a few small rust spots, and minor mechanical dilemmas.
The rifle itself has a DPMS adjustable stock, a flip up (2 sizes) rear peep sight and a 'flipable' front sight, so it can be a post or a "V". It does show some wear, but is fully functional and ready to go. There are a few spall rust spots, but nothing scary. The thumb safety apparently has a broken spring, IT DOES WORK, but it does not stay where you put it, if you shoulder the weapon, it swings into the 'Fire' position, but if you stand it straight up, it swings into 'safe' position. I thought it was kind of handy like that, so I never fixed it. I have never put a scope on it, but with the open sights, it is pretty darn accurate.

It comes with 2 magazines: 1 is a Colt 20 round capacity, and 2 is a Center Industries Corp. 30 round capacity.

Also included is 10 - 30 round boxes (300pcs) of 5.56 X 45 ammo This is NEW ammo, not reloads, they were repacked from bulk (by me) into these new 30 round boxes. 7 1/2 boxes are Sellior and Bellot, 2 1/2 boxes are Lake City. All of the ammo is 62gr Full Metal Jacket - Steel Core - Boat Tail, complete with Green Tips. I think the Military Designation is SS-109, they are nicknamed 'penetrator' rounds. NOT Armor Piercing, but you will get your point across pretty well with them.

This is a package deal for $850.00, complete, you can go shooting with it tomorrow.

title: For Sale:  Mosin Nagant 91/30 (2) M44 (1)
postcontent:
I have three excellent condition Mosin Nagant rifles for sale. Will sell separately or as a package. I am firm on my prices - it's what I have in them. Each of these are unique in their own way. 

Top rifle is a 1938 Izhevsk 91/30 import marks shows Century Arms International. All this rifle needs is a cleaning rod, forward end cap needs blued, and the rear sight spring is missing. The most compelling feature of this rifle is the bent bolt - it appears done here in the states, and was a nice job. Gives the appearance of a former sniper, but this is not a former sniper. The stock is impeccable on this rifle, and the finish appears to be arsenal finish based on the stock markings. The stock has multiple interesting stampings. The receiver, magazine floor plate and butt plate all have matching numbers. The bolt numbers were ground off whenever someone did the bent bolt modification. 
The bore on this rifle is like new. I have $185 in this rifle and I am not budging off it.

The middle rifle is the most interesting of the three. 1936 Izhevsk 91/30 with no import marks at all. This rifle is believed to be in the US since at least the early 1960's or maybe earlier. Brought in before import markings were mandated. The receiver, bolt and magazine floor plate all have matching numbers. The butt plate is not numbered. This rifle, like the 1938 Izhevsk, are both from the manufacture era in the USSR when the Spanish Civil War was going on. Neither 91/30 show any evidence of SCW duty. This 91/30, although no SA (Finnish) markings exist, has Finn written all over it. The one piece stock is Finn, and has marks and an engraving that just yells interest. The sling hangers and sling are Finn, as is the front sight. The barrel bands are M91 type 1 bands - the earliest made - and are no later than 1910. The front barrel band is in place with the wood screw the Finns used, and the rear band holds itself in place with a small plastic shim I cut and installed. The stock has evidence of a rear band screw at one time, and what's left of the screw is still in the stock. If this rifle could tell history imagine the story it could tell. The only thing this rifle needs is a cleaning rod, and I've not found the right rod to match the aesthetics. The bore is excellent, and I am firm on $250 for this rifle.

The third and final rifle I am offering for sale is my M44. 1945 Izhevsk complete, except it needs a cleaning rod. Bayonet stows and extends fine, and the bore is like a mirror on this rifle. Numbers match on this rifle for everything except the bolt. Complete with sling, the only other aspect of this rifle is the stock has some battle wear, the down side being one area above the trigger on right side which was an attempted repair. You  know that T-53's are all over the place and M44's are getting harder to find. This rifle is also a Century Arms import. I am firm on $225 for this rifle, and you know that's the fair price in our local market.

I would be glad to send more pictures and description on request. I am willing to FTF in the Cranberry, Moon / Airport or Harmarville areas as I frequent those areas. Must show valid PA drivers license to prove PA residency. Please feel free to contact me here or at seven two four nine nine one eight eight five three and I text too.   

Thanks for looking.

title: For Sale:  Joe the Plumber/Circa 2017.
postcontent:
Only weeks after leaving office, Barack Obama discovers a leak in his house, so he calls Joe the Plumber to come out and fix it.  Joe drives to Obama's new house, which is located in a very exclusive gated community where all the residents are quite affluent  and make generally more than $250,000 per year.  Joe arrives and is escorted to the guest bathroom that contains the leaky pipe under the sink.  Joe assesses the problem and tells Obama that it's an easy repair that will likely take less than 10 minutes.  Obama asks Joe how much it will cost.

Joe checks his rate chart and says, "$9,500".  "What?!  $9,500"?, Obama asks,
stunned, "But you said it's an easy repair!" Joe says, "Yes, but the new way is to charge those who make $250,000 per year much more so I can fix the plumbing of less fortunate people for free", explains Joe.  "This has always been my philosophy.  As a matter of fact, I lobbied the Democratic lead Congress, who passed this philosophy into law.  Now all plumbers must do business this way.  It's known as the 'Affordable Plumbing Act of 2014.'  I’m Surprised you haven't heard of it."

In spite of that, Obama tells Joe there's no way he's paying that much for a small plumbing repair, so Joe leaves after placing the bill for the service call on the entry table.  Obama spends the next hour flipping through the phone book & checking Craigslist for other plumbers, but he finds that all local plumbing services have gone out of business.  Not wanting to pay Joe's price & succumb to the newly instituted business trends, Obama does nothing and the leak goes unrepaired for several more days and, of course, becomes worse.  A week later the leak is so bad that a bucket has to be placed under the sink.  Michelle is not happy as guests will be arriving the next morning.  The situation quickly becomes worse and this bucket needs to be emptied repeatedly, and there's an increased risk that the room will flood, so they call Joe again to explain their predicament and plead with him to return.

Joe goes back to re-examine the leaky pipe, checks his updated Union rate chart and says, “Let's see, this will now cost you $21,000."  Obama quickly fires back, "What!  A few days ago your price was $9,500!"  Joe explains, "Well, because of the 'Affordable Plumbing Act', a lot of higher-income people are now learning how to maintain and take care of their own plumbing, so there are fewer payers into the plumbing exchanges.  As a result and as you should easily understand, the price I have to charge higher-income people like you keeps rising.  Not only that, but for some odd reason the demand for plumbing work by those who get it for free has skyrocketed unbelievably!  There's a long waiting list of those who need repairs, but the amount we receive is far short of covering our costs.  This unfortunately has put a lot of my fellow plumbers out of business, they're not being replaced, and nobody is learning the plumbing trade any more because they know they can't make any money at it.  I'm hurting, too, thanks to greedy rich people like you who won't pay their fair share."

Obama says, "Joe!  This looks pretty bad.  If all the rich people learn how to fix and maintain their own plumbing and you can't charge the poorer people, you'll likely go broke!  What will you do then?"

Joe replies, "I've been thinking of becoming a Community Organizer & see what happens after that."

From the country, (Croatia), that has brought the American shooter the highly popular Springfield HD series of semi-automatic pistols, comes their first semi- automatic 9m/m (9X19m/m) caliber pistol, the PHP MV 9. The designation PHV stands for Prvi Hrvastski Pistolj, or first Croatian pistol. It was developed in Croatia in the early 1990’s during the counties war for independence and was produced in a long barrel version, (PHP MV 17), and this shorter barrel, compact model, (PHP MV 9). Local purchase information:
All federal and state laws apply. Buyer must complete ATF form 4473 and pass a standard background check in person. 6.5% Ohio sales tax will be collected from Ohio buyer. Out of State purchase information:
We will complete out of state sales by transferring the gun to your local FFL holder who will then complete the paperwork and background check. Shipping is normally $25 for handguns and $35 for long guns, which covers packaging, shipping costs, tracking numbers, and insurance to most of the lower 48 states. Warranty and Return information:
If there is a manufacturing defect, the repair will be handled by the manufacturer's warranty.

Contact us:
Please contact David Greer with Free Republic Firearms at REDACTED or by phone at REDACTED with any questions. We are located in Massillon, Ohio. To get updates of our new arrivals, "like" our Facebook page, and visit www.freerepublicfirearms.com for more information. If you contact us via email, please include your name and phone number to eliminate spammers and to ensure we can contact you. Occasionally we have problems with messages from hidden email addresses that are sent through gun listing/auction sites. Our reply emails are being returned as undeliverable, so if we don't respond to your email, please make sure we have another way to contact you.  We do not hold firearms, magazines, and accessories, because people do not always follow through with the purchase. Items are sold on a first come; first serve basis.

Trades:
We will consider trades from local, in-person buyers, but we cannot give a value on a gun unless we see it in person. Most of our firearms are new, and we are very selective about what used firearms we sell.   Please realize will cannot pay full retail for your firearm. We are a business, and there has to be room for us to make a small amount when we resell the firearm.  Let us know what you have to trade, and we will let you know if it is something we need.  If you are an out of state buyer, we will not consider a trade. 

About us:
Free Republic Firearms is a family owned FFL dealer located in Massillon Ohio. We are dedicated to supplying quality firearms, ammunition, and accessories to responsible gun owners for the purposes of self-defense, recreation, hunting, shooting sports, and collections.

We seek to make products affordable for our customers by stocking products that our customers need, rather than incur the costs of huge inventories, and large payrolls. Unlike large retailers, we keep our costs low by using our suppliers’ inventories to supplement our inventory. We bring additional products into our inventory as our customers need them, and pass on the savings of our low overhead costs to you.

We believe in providing firearms to responsible people who understand the importance of the 2nd Amendment, and the responsibility we have to protect it.  We are not interested in supplying firearms to those in society who do not have the morals, maturity, and character to be responsible gun owners.  It is our right to refuse to sell firearms to any person. We are interested in arming responsible citizens so that they can defend themselves against the criminal element, not arming the criminal element of society.

Extra information:
To all the spammers and criminals that can't legally buy guns, don't contact us asking to meet in a parking lot to complete a cash sale, or to trade a stolen laptop or other electronics for our guns. You shouldn't have guns, and we're definitely not going to help you get one.  To those who are under the legal age to buy firearms or handguns, we understand your desire to have a gun, but we will not break the law to sell you one, so please don't ask. We believe that if an 18 year old is old enough to fight for our country in the armed forces, they should be able to buy a gun. But until a little common sense is used in Washington DC, we cannot sell handguns to anyone under 21, and long guns to anyone under 18.
